-- Algonquin Buys 109.5-Megawatt Illinois Wind Farm from Goldwind
-- B y   W i l l   W a d e
-- 2013-01-02T14:15:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-02/algonquin-buys-109-5-megawatt-illinois-wind-farm-from-goldwind.html
Algonquin Power & Utilities Corp. (AQN) , a
Canadian renewable-energy producer, purchased a 109.5-megawatt
wind farm in Illinois from China’s Xinjiang Goldwind Science &
Technology Co.  Algonquin paid $148.9 million for the Shady Oaks project
about 80 kilometers (50 miles) west of  Chicago , the Oakville,
Canada-based company said in a statement today.  Shady Oaks was completed in June and is selling electricity
to  Exelon Corp. (EXC) ’s Commonwealth Edison under a 20-year contract.
Goldwind will be responsible for operating the plant.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
